msg: For FSFS format 7, eliminate P2L index lookups when not in block-read mode.
The block-read code path always performs a two-way lookup because the
reader sub-functions expect a full item description (P2L entry) instead
of just a location to read from.  Therefore, we should simply skip the
whole block_read() code path when not in block-read mode; our addressing
has been unified across all formats anyway with a the change paths list
(use_block_read): New utility predicate deciding what code path to take.
read_delta_window): Use new function to select code path.
(svn_fs_fs__get_changes): Same. However, for the normal read path, we
need format-specific code to get the offset.
(block_read): No checking for block-read mode needed here anymore.
